    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-02T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="800"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.616/348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1941-11-02T19:00:00+03:00">November 2, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 3—1:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1867. For the President, the Secretary and the Under Secretary. My 1864, November
                    1, 7 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d800fn23">Not printed.</note> I called on
                    Vyshinski today and requested him to transmit to Stalin the President’s
                        message<note n="24" xml:id="d800fn24">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> which I conveyed to him orally. Vyshinski requested me to leave the text
                    with him as he said he assumed Stalin would wish to make an appropriate reply. I
                    did not feel justified in complying with his request as to have done so would
                    have compromised our Navy Department code. I have, however, sent him an <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> containing a carefully prepared paraphrase
                    of the message which I believe will satisfy him. If it is desired that I furnish
                    him with the text, I should appreciate instructions to this effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
